articles.title: About this site
articles.contents:
About Me
I’m going to just use something I wrote in a tutorial a few days ago
as my introduction for now. Hello! My name is Rachel
Heiss, and I’m a home schooled sophomore in high school. I’m
currently in Kane’s Free High
School Data Science Bootcamp, which is why I’m making this practice
website. I have five younger siblings and live near Atlanta, Georgia. I
enjoy reading, writing, baking, Marvel movies, and listening to
musicals, podcasts, and Taylor Swift.
Contact Me
Email: rachelheiss@gmail.com
GitHub: rachelheiss

articles.title: Economic Connectedness
articles.description: This website is practice for my final project. There are just two graphs on here, and they examine the relationship between economic connectedness and population.
